caption: Yup good breakfast / brunch. Small but comfortable. Out door dinning. Great service. Cajun french toast. . Coffee. Lemon crepe. Mimosa. Omelette and relaxing family time. Great place right in the French Quarter. 🇺🇸❤️🥘🍸🍋

This is the only place to go for a rib sticking meal to start your day.  Service is good,  friendly, portions are big and food is great and priced right.  Best grits in the FQ. Chicken and waffles are ridiculous.
Breakfast was amazing,  the toast is to die for! Omelettes are great, homemade biscuits, yummy! And the service is impeccable!

Ordered a crepe, pancake balls, potatoes, and some tea to warm up from the rain. After tasting a few bites of food a very comfortable bug started leisurely scurrying across the bench I was seated in. Was unable to finish my food so unable to provide a thorough review.

I put my name on the online wait list and it stated it would be about an hour wait, which was totally fine. Later, I get a call that my request for a table near a window may not be able to be fulfilled, which was understandable and I agreed to take seats at the bar or whatever becomes available first. The app tells me to go check in at the restaurant, so we did. The host tells us that they'll text us once our table is ready. We left to go check out some stores and we finally get a text our table is ready. We arrive at the restaurant again and there is one couple in front of us at the host's desk. The host goes to seat that couple, and I happen to see that my name was before theirs on the wait list. The host returns and I give her my name. She looks at the list, sees that there are no more tables open, and by the look on her face I see that she realized she just gave our table away. It's been well over an hour as this point. I said aloud to my boyfriend that they just gave our table away. The host says our table isn't ready yet. Then why did I get a text 5 minutes ago stating that it was? The manager (I think) steps in and covers their mistake by saying, "You wanted a table by a window, right?" On the phone I clearly stated that I would take whatever becomes available first. So we wait another 10-15 minutes. We were so hungry that we hoped the food would make up for this, but we were wrong. The food was mediocre and one side of my stuffed French toast was too burnt for consumption. There are better places to eat breakfast in this beautiful city.

Hands down the best french toast I have ever had. If you come to the French Quarter, this is a MUST! Super friendly and fast service. I simply could not have been more pleased! My husbands omelette was also amazing! Thanks Johnny for your awesome service!

Normally visit the Gentilly location. However, this one does not disappoint. My favorite dish is their chicken and waffles. We also ordered the coconut cream french toast. Everything was amazing. There was a mix up  with our waitlist spot, someone tried to tell me we were not on the list after they called our table. After waiting for over an hour, that was pretty aggravating. Other than that, great food and great service.

The worst brunch we had in New Orleans. Savory crepe with goat cheese was watery and extremely sour, to the point where I couldn’t eat it. Aebleskivers were undercooked. Steak eggs potatoes - meat had a funky taste to it, like the steak wasn’t fresh, and potatoes tasted like they were cooked yesterday. Overall food was of very poor quality.
Outstanding food,  great prices too!
If you ever in the quarters in Nolan's. Stopping and enjoy the meals is was delicious. The food was delicious the staff was excellent on helping you. You won't be disappointed.🥳😍

One of the greatest breakfast places in the United States. The food is authentic and the prices are unbeatable. I went twice and did not regret any of the delicious calories. The staff is joyful and precise. The wait is long, but the virtue of patience pays off! Please do not go to the French quarter without eating here. You will regret it. Thank you French Toast, with love from Anchorage Alaska.
Great food, reasonable prices for French Quarter. Everyone was very nice.
Excellent food
This place! OMG! The portions are huge. The food is delicious, full of flavor. I will come back tomorrow again
Excellent!
This place was excellent ! My wife and I went there twice for breakfast that’s how good it was ! Highly recommend.
Great service and food. Nice day to be outside. Leftovers for later.😷🤓
The king cake french toast was amazing! Will be back next time I am in NOLA

If you need a serious French toast fix this is definitely your place! Bread variety great Gruyere omelet great Avocado toast great Been here several times and they never let me down. Grits and bacon great I wish I took a picture but the food was so good I couldn't wait. Tip: Get on the waiting list--you can thank me later.

(Translated by Google) The excellent and hearty chocolate strawberry crèpe. And a good hot chocolate!  (Original) La crèpe fraises chocolat excellente et copieuse. Et un bon chocolat chaud !

I already knew what we were going to order! We ordered the king cake stuffed french toast, chicken and waffles, and bacon It was amazing and so delicious!! Everything was cooked perfectly and presented well. Staff were so helpful, friendly and service oriented. Will definitely be back and recommend to others

Delicious! They have some classic southern favorites and some new twists on old favorites. I’m a classic girl, an I opted for their traditional southern breakfast and I was completely satisfied with everything!  If you plan to visit on a weekend morning, be prepared for a wait. It’s located near tons of other shops and just a short walk down from the river, so you’ll have plenty to see and do while waiting.  The service was good and I didn’t feel rushed, even though they were very busy and had many people waiting. Very relaxed atmosphere, with wonderful menu options.  Next time I’m in Nola, I’ll be sure to come back for more deliciousness!
Had the French Toast with a side of bacon - excellent! And it's attached to our favorite hotel in NOLA, The Hotel Provincial. Definately recommend.
Cute little spot pumping out some serious breakfast. Amazing stuffed French toast. Great coffee. Friendly staff. Highly recommend!!
Best grits ever
Best grits I've ever had!!!   Crepe with strawberries and chocolate was also delicious.
Very good pricing for the meals! My wife had the omelette with ratatouille while I had french toast king cake. My wife loves her meal and I enjoyed mine as well!
Amazing food and ambiance!
Service was great! Very attentive without being pushy. King cake French toast was amazing and they offer very generous portion sizes!
Awesome food and great staff! This was our first stop when we got into town.

Soooo good! Everyone we asked recommended here and they were spot on. The biscuits, bacon, homemade jam, and just about everything else is rave-worthy.  We actually ended up going back twice and it was super sweet that the staff remembered us - cheers to them!  Everything was super clean and sanitation appeared to be a top priority. One Tip: they ask that you wear your mask at the table while you're ordering which we did and encourage others to do the same. The Bloody Mary looked awesome and I hope to try it next time!

This place is one of my new found favorites! The french toast meals there are AMAZING! I’ve never had such big slices before, i am telling you now that it will fill you up. The coffee as well as the Avo and egg on toast was to die for and the service is good, right now you just call in and “make a reservation” and they’re pretty good with letting you know how long you’ll be waiting (take a walk around the French Market). I gave them 3 stars though because they will charge you for ANYTHING extra. I asked for some mayonnaise for my Avocado and she charged me almost a dollar extra :/ - other than that I totally recommend stopping by! Its also a little bit opposite Café Du Monde.
Small place with a unique menu and a popular reputation. We waited quite a while to have their savory stuffed crepes, worth it! Our second time here and we'll be back next time we are in town.
Amazing food & staff.
The food is really good here! I visited twice during my weekend in New Orleans. The staff are also really welcoming and friendly!
Delicious breakfast! Loved everything we had. Love the different flavor options for mimosas.
A touch pricey, but hey... you're in the Quarter.  Omelet was delicious.

Kind service and great food! We ordered the fried oyster toast and added a catfish and the ham, mushroom, and gruyere crepe. Our server was Meghan and she was very kind and attentive. Recommend for sure (reserve a spot on the website to save wait time)!

Like there's nothing really new or unique on their menu. And while it tastes good it can be a repeater for locals, but I think tourists should find another place. But for a COVID restricted place this is the best in the city.

We were excited to eat here, after reading rave reviews online, except for a few. Sadly, I am adding to the number of bad reviews. Hiring a competent hostess would help. We came back close to the end of our wait time.We were a party of two, and we watched as several larger parties that were behind us were seated before us. We inquired at the host stand, and she told us that there were three more parties in front of us. When we told her that both those parties were behind us, she got argumentative. Was staying at the hotel behind this restaurant and came here twice for breakfast on weekdays. Didn’t have to wait, and the service was pleasant. Never had an empty coffee cup. First day I had the ratatouille omelette which I enjoyed,  it a friend had the chicken and waffles which were amazing. Second day we sat at the bar and I indulged I. The chicken and waffles. They are seriously some of the beat chicken and waffles I’ve ever had. The chicken was juicy, hot and crispy and the waffles were light and delicate. The spicy butter it’s served with really ties it all together. I highly recommend this dish. It would also be a good appetizer for 4 people who just want a taste. The aebleskivers are fun and delicious. They’re like a softer pancakier beignet. I really enjoyed the lemon curd ones.
Great food you won't go wrong here.
Do yourself a favor and get the fried oysters toast!

I love this place.  Not only is the food extraordinary but the operation itself is so professionally run its amazing.  My dish was absolutely fabulous and beautiful as well.  I could eat here every day!!
the food we had was amazing a must try 6 stars
Food was amazing service was on point and I loved the atmosphere the reggae playing in the background was really chill, great experience.
Absolutely delicious! We went there three times on our vacation.  French toast, crepes, omelettes, chicken and waffles were all delicious!
Excellent personable service...waffles were a bit overcooked

We sat at the bar! The bartender Lucie was very helpful since we have never been before. Per her recommendation, we ordered Coconut French Toast and Oyster Toast... OMG... the taste was indescribable. Must go if you are looking for a brunch place!
We loved our brunch. I ate a savory crepe and my boyfriend ate a sweet crepe. Both were delicious. We met Justine at a local park and she recommended we stop in, glad we did!
(Translated by Google) Very tasty crepes. And they are very granded  (Original) Muy rico los crepes. Y son muy granded
Delicious food, good drinks, and great service.
Great service. Food was amazing and the latte was the perfect temperature. Recommended!
I ate way more than I should have because it was just that good. Large portions. Busy, check in ahead of time. Well worth the trip and the wait.
King Cake French Toast was amazing. Strawberry and Chocolate Crepe fantastic. Wait staff friendly as ask of New Orleans is.
Great food
Pretty good breakfast place. Love the Chicken.
Amazing place
Great location...be prepared to wait because it's popular but worth it. Food was yummy and had a variety of interesting choices which I love.
Good food , get there early it gets busy fast. The chicken and waffles were amazing.

Wish we could give 10 stars- Easily my favorite meal of our trip. The service was quick, thoughtful, and friendly, and the food was all amazing! We had the croque Madame, the aebleskivers, crepes, and the chicken and waffles. One of those meals you’re angry at because it’s so delicious and has to end!!
Looks good but after being told it was a 20 minutes wait. We left after 50 minute. Got the texy that our table was ready after an hour. If its an hour wait just tell me.
Great place great food great mimosas! Gruyère is especially good!

Came across this breakfast spot while out this morning immediately seated.  The food was wonderful and neither my husband and I were able to finish our meal.  Highly recommend.  Also the staff was very helpful and nice.
Amazing food, best brandy milk punch in the city, great service.
Good food.  Not too expensive.  It is a small place.  So at times there can be a wait for a table.
Amazing breakfast, sooo good
Outstanding chicken.... <3
Great dishes, good imagination! Staff was exceptional even with a full restaurant. We are making it a must do for every visit to New Orleans.
Food is top of the line had the stuffed French toast with pineapple. And hands down the best French toast I've ever had.

Waited an hour and a half to be seated. Staff was wide-eyed and seemingly incapable. Food was dry and uninspired. Seriously, you'd do better enjoying the continental breakfast at your hotel. Which is a total shame, because i've enjoyed many a good plate at their fairgrounds location. Essentially this is Toast banking on name-sake and location; a page from The Ruby Slipper's book.

My group went here twice during our trip to New Orleans because the food was so good. I had the breakfast sandwich on the first visit and the chicken sandwich the following time. Both were cooked to perfection and everything else we ordered was great as well. It does get pretty busy though so don't be surprised if you have to wait a little while to get a table.
Service was very slow and order was incorrect.  Food was good but not great.

The restaurant was only about half full on a Tuesday at noon and we couldn't get our server back to save our lives... there was staff all over but it was like no one was actually doing anything. I asked for a coffee refill and they took my coffee cup and never came back- I had to go to the bar and ask for a new cup of coffee. The tables on both sides of us were very unhappy with their food. I was really disappointed based on all the good reviews.
Solid breakfast all day joint. Good enough food and very reasonable prices. Nice staff
Small footprint, but big taste. I took the family here and we shared a couple of sweet and a couple of their salty crepes as well as their omelette. Their latte was also very good.
Really great breakfast spot with an absolutely delicious coconut cream french toast. Awesome coffee too.

The menu looks amazing and has great options but is any food really worth the price if the service is slow and your food sits under the heat lamp for 10 minutes? Maybe it's just me but I dont like a warm side salad or fruit...  I was served at the bar where I could see my food on the counter but no servers were picking up there orders. The location is a small restaurant. I was not the only one recieving terrible service. My friend didnt even receive the side order of egg she asked for.  After finishing off our waters and stairing at our waitress we hoped she would come by and refill us after 5 minutes we got up and grab ourselves water.  Finally done with French toast and the service we wanted to leave and let other people who were waisting there time in line that wrapped all the way outside there chance to be disappointed.  After another 10 minutes and raising our hand, we got the check. We handed over our 3 credit cards and asked to pay for our own meal instead she split the bill 3 ways.  The 3 of us that sat at the bar arrived 5 mins after they opened. We left after 1 and 20mins. Clearly the people who work here at a breakfast restaurant are not morning people.  ***Take my review with a grain of salt I experience my service the day after Mardi gras***
This was the best french toast ever.
Long wait ... suggest to get on the waiting list early ... food was super awesome ... delicious ... wow
Great coffee, fresh nice food def recommend
Very quaint with great breakfast food. Give it a try.
Oh so darn good! Chicken n Waffles Fantastic!
Great breakfast Nook.  My wife really enjoyed the variety customer sevice is the best. We will return !!!.
Best chicken I've ever had
Delicious crepes and solid food
Amazing breakfast!!!!
Great food and wonderful French toast. Music is too loud though.
A nice stop in for breakfast while staying at the adjacent hotel.

Just had a wonderful NOLA breakfast at Toast!  We will be back to try it again as there are numerous awesome dishes on the menu. Friendly servers and awesome people willing to share a little time with you.  Chicken and waffles were awesome as well as a hell of a bloody Maria. Sausage biscuit with gravy was yummy!! I do suggest adding your name to the wait list before you arrive.
Decent breakfast. Decent service. Wait is forever on weekends.

Pro tip: go on to their site and get on the waiting list so you aren't standing in line waiting forever to get a table. I took a pic of the French toast.. I was buzzing on the sugar for hours. Holy cow was that good. Plenty of other breakfast options too. Coffee was always kept hot. Probably the closet thing to a refined, old fashioned, soda fountain shop I've been in for some time. You'll definitely want to eat here once if you are in town on a visit.
Wow Oyster and Maux chou toast was great as was prosciutto and ricotta toast.
disgusting kitchen, unsanitary
Scrumptious breakfast foods here close to being decadent..conveniently located right in the French Quarter  by Joanie on the pony. Service was quick and friendly. Loved our waiter Justin!!!
Get the avocado toast. It's amazingly good.
I visited two Toast locations and neither disappointed. You should eat here when in town.

Great simple breakfasts done right.  The French toast with fruit was very good, the slices were thick and crispy on the outside, creamy on the inside.  The crepes were substantial and well made.  The only minor complaint I have is that for the French toast with fruit, the "fruit" was simply a handful of blueberries.  Could have used more/a variety of berries.
Friendly staff and an awesome menu. Had to go with a savory crepe this time but hope to be back for the French toast

Really the best breakfast we've ever had. We decided last minute to check it out and it was absolutely worth it! We loved everything. The service was fabulous. The food was delicious. Just go... you can thank me later ;)
Super love this place so much! Great food every time and I'm in here often. The prices are prefect, in a city where every other dish is expensive as hell.
Delicious food and massive french toast.
Fantastic food and fantastic prices. Enjoy
Walking down French market district. And fell into this little jem!! French Toast big as Texas !! Order the fruit French toast and the potatoes great place !!
Awesome breakfast spot. Great food and great price. Be warned the lattes are sweet, but no worries still great.

I make this a regular stop when it's not too busy. It's super popular and not very big so it fills up fast, but its worth it. The crepes, omelettes, and various toast options are all excellent. The service is usually very friendly and now that the liquor license is cleared you can even get yourself a wake up cocktail. If you happen to be there on one of the days that they do breakfast tacos (or they might call them burritos...) for the special I absolutely recommend that you take them up on that offer.

The food was good and filling. The waiters were nice. I love the fact that you can get on the waitlist via an app. However, the waiter took a long time before coming to ask for our order. Then it took a long time for our food to come out, apparently there was a problem with the waffle maker. Overall good experience though!

A cute place with a friendly, laid back wait staff. Sadly for me, the berry french toast was very dry and too dark - almost burnt. The Berries consisted of around 10 blueberries. My husband had the fried chicken biscuit which he said was very good. Perhaps an off day? We will try some where else tomorrow.

Great place for breakfast!  Crepes, omelets, and  French toast.  Actually they have almost all types of breakfast. We went here a few times: the second item I had was French toast.  Man it was really good!  And the coffee flows freely here.  I'd recommend!
Delicious ! I took the pineapple and coconut french toast and I recommand it !

We stayed across the street at a near by hotel. We went to eat with a group of 7 (which we know is a lot). Got told the wait would be between 30-45 min, ok, great. Ended up waiting right under an hour before we decided to place our order to go since they told us it would be another 45 min before we could be seated. We got the food, and it was standard French toast, eggs etc, nothing too special.  One person ordered steak and it was extremely undercooked. He goes back to get the steak fixed, which they do. But when he asked for a refill of juice so he can drink with his breakfast (since it took a while to fix) they said that would be extra money. Long story short, not great customer service. You could tell they were stretched thin. The only reason I give two stars is because you could tell the hostess felt bad for our wait.

Came with a larger party and was given a reasonable wait time estimate. We watched as group after group seated before us. We asked for an update on the time and were told another 45 minutes after waiting 30. We dicided to order to go. Food was made promptly. We sat down to eat nearby, most of it was good and hot. However, one meal was steak and it was raw. The order was made again but no compensation was offered, they would not even refill the drink associated with the meal (it normally does not get refills, but it would be the least they could do).  In short, pretty good food, poor service, and undercooked food incident that I'll assume only occurred because it was a very busy day.
Food is tasty.  Waiter was ethical.  I'd come back
Great place, amazing food.

Well who would not want to eat at a restaurant named after a famous New Orleans dish- Pain Perdu? Let me begin by saying the building and décor are beautiful old French New Orleans. The space felt very pleasing, sunny, and inviting. The staff..... well bless their hearts, they seemed lost in the headlights. The food was sub-par for New Orleans where you better be good buddy or adios. So we both started with plain jane lattes which we both found to be quite good. I ask the waitress some specifics about our delicious lattes and her response was....." it comes from a machine over there". Well I delved a little deeper and she simply was lost in the headlights again. Anyway we both had savory crepes- me Florentine and my spouse Mushroom, onion, peppers, spinach, and chevre. Now I  have eaten my fair share of crepes in the past (Defunct Petunias in the Quarter served divine, light crepes) and these things were somewhere between an omelet and a crepe and not really to my liking. I must say the ingredients of the crepe themselves were somewhat complex and tasty. It was like a different taste sensation with each bite. The side dish of fruit was good and the sunny side eggs came out as I ordered. My spouse had over easy eggs and he did not experience horrific gastritis as did I a few hours after leaving the Quarter, so I suspect that my eggs were just a bit too under cooked. Another thing I liked about French Toast was that they brought out a carafe of iced water which reminded me of Paris as did the décor to some extent. So to summarize: the décor is lovely, the staff is rather inexperienced, the food was overall average, and the bill was mid-range.

Absolutely the best breakfast we have ever had!!! Everything was perfect! The service was amazing and the atmosphere is great. Very cute little NOLA spot! We can't wait to go back. You know it's good when weeks later you can't stop talking about it!
Amazing service and teamwork
Pancake balls with a long name. Starts with an A. Totally delicious. Aerslivkes?  Delicious.
Terrible food , terrible service. Too noisy!!!
I had the classic breakfast, that was fine my friend had chicken and waffles and the chicken was raw. The staff made it again and it was perfect.
Deliciously chicken & waffles!!! Great place
Can I just tell you this place is fabulous!!  Nothing is going to dish up a better toast! I’m so impressed. Clean and friendly.  Small perfect menu!!!
Food took forever, horrible coffee. They forgot one of our party’s sandwich’s. So much staff and not the proper service. The food is not good. Go somewhere else.

Related to the other Toast restaurants, this comfy old school diner with a modern french New Orleans flavor will amaze you with delectible sweet crepes and stuffed french toast, savory sandwiches and omlettes and friendly staff that will make you feel welcome and delightfully filled up. THIS is what real New Orleans is all about.
